<p>Clients who miss three (3) consecutive sessions (group or individual) will be discharged. Fatherhood Campaign – BIPP is not responsible for absences; it is the client’s responsibility to make up or reschedule any missing sessions. Supervising officer, judge, or court determines case outcomes related to absences.</p>
<p>There are no excused absences. Incarceration is an inexcusable absence. Any charges filed regarding any offense related to domestic violence is an automatic dismissal.</p>
<p>If you have a cell phone it must be turned off or on silent and placed out of sight; text messaging is not allowed.</p>
<p>No food allowed in group room or virtual meeting.</p>
<p>If you destroy or damage property, you will be liable for the damages.</p>
<p>Restroom breaks should take no longer than 5 minutes unless you have prior approval from BIPP staff.</p>
<p>Payment for services is due at the time service is rendered. All services must be paid; you should have a zero balance to receive proof of completion. Attendance may exceed 24 weeks if payment is not completed.</p>
<p>This building is designated as a Non-Smoking facility or virtual meeting.</p>
<p>I agree to arrive to all sessions on time. If I arrive more than 10 minutes after the start time, I will not receive credit for attending the group.</p>
<p>I understand I must sign the group attendance roster (or check in during the virtual meeting) in order to receive credit; otherwise I will not be counted present.</p>
<p>I will notify Fatherhood Campaign – BIPP of any change of address or phone numbers.</p>
<p>All homework assignments must be completed. Clients will not receive credit for incomplete assignments.</p>
<p>I agree to contact BIPP at 210-664-0102 in the event of absences. Failure to contact BIPP within two (2) consecutive absences is an automatic dismissal.</p>
<p>I agree not to attend group (including virtual) under the influence of alcohol or illegal drugs. If substance use is suspected, I may be asked to complete a drug and/or alcohol test; results are reported to Fatherhood Campaign – BIPP.</p>
<p>I agree not to be abusive toward any staff or participants; I will not use sexist or racist language.</p>
<p>I agree not to possess a weapon of any kind while at Fatherhood Campaign – BIPP and to follow all federal and state firearm restriction laws related to domestic violence offenses.</p>
<p>I agree to respect the confidentiality rights of other group participants; breach of confidentiality jeopardizes participation and may result in removal from the program and reporting to proper authorities.</p>
<p>I agree to notify a staff person of any and all emergencies that I am either a part of or a witness to.</p>
<p>Fatherhood Campaign – BIPP is committed to establishing non-violence in families. It is the main goal of these psycho-educational classes.</p>
